message.body: Haha you sound ridiculous. I always touch public doorknobs barehandedÂ
Are you working today?
Yeah. Every day except Sunday.
What time?
Awwww man!
Why? You there now?

Well it's kind of a stretch but I saw on Facebook that your friend Molly is doing a rendition of Madea at Penn later today. I want to see that. Plus, there will be pizza afterwards :) but you have work.
How much and what time?
I think it's free. It didn't say a price. 5z
I don't know if it's free. Let me see if I can find info
Wait hahaha she's not doing Madea. She's doing Medea
Oh sorry, spelled it wrong. Either ways, it's the Greek play I want to see.
Not Tyler Perry!
Haha well i wouldnt take off work for that. Sorry.
I figured. For the record, I did say "it's kind of a stretch" because I know you!
Well madea's not a stretch haha that's why I was about to go
That Madea would be a stretch for me.
Did you go?
No, it would have been weird to go by myself. That was the point of me asking you.
Oh okay. Sorry
Hahah it's okay. I went out to go run errands with Tam anyways.

Also, I'm in the theater-going mood and there's a play at Penn that I saw on their theater website months ago for a play called "In the Next Room". It seems good and I'm looking at tickets. Interested?
Sure do you have any more details?
